  "text": "Cross-correlation analyses provide an indication of the degree of synchronous activity between single neurons and has been used extensively to examine synaptic interactions among elements of the neural population [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Activity recorded from neurons at different electrode placements were analyzed using cross-correlograms for lead/lag times of 100 ms and a 2 ms bin width. The cross-correlation coefficients were calculated as described in [CITATION_3] .",
